div1.p: United States District Court Western District of Washington Northern Division
In the Matter of the Petition of Arthur B. Martin for a Writ of Habeas Corpus } No. 2852
Order Dismissing Petition and Writ of Habeas Corpus

This matter coming on for hearing on the petition and writ of Habeas Corpus, and the return thereto, and the petitioner appearing in person, and the respondent, Henry M. White appearing by his attorneys;

It is appering to the court that Fifty Dollars has been deposited with the respondent, belonging to the petitioner, and that the Clerk's costs in the sum of Eleven and Sixty One Hundredths Dollars, and Marshal's fees in the sum of Two and twenty-four Hundredths Dollars, and the sum of Eight Dollars, cost of maintence of petitioner during the month of October, 1914, shouldall be paid from said sum of Fifty Dollars;
The Court having heard arguments of the petitioner and of counsel for resondent, and being fully advised in the premises:

Wherefore, it is hereby ordered that the petition and the writ of habeas corpus be and the same hereby are forever discharge and dismissed, and that the petition and is hereby remanded to the custody of the Immigration Authorities;

p.add: appearing that the petitioner has on deposit with the commissioner of Immigration the sum of fifty dollars and that he has withheld this proceeding in forma pauperis it is

div1.p:
And it is further ordered that the said Henry M. White, Commissioner of Immigration respondent, pay to the Clerk of the United States District
Court the clerks costs in this proceeding the said sum of $11.60 his costs herein; and that he pay to the United States Marshal said sum of $2.24; and that he pay the sum of $8.,The necessary expense paid by the U.S. for the maintenance of the petitioner pending hid hearing the cost of maintenance, to the parties entiled therebe; and that the balance of the money on deposit be paid to the petitioner.
div1.ab: Jeremiah Neterer United States District Judge.
div1.p: In the District Court of the United States for the Western District of Washington LoB-5-120
In the Matter of the Petition of Athur B. Martin for a Writ of Habeas Corpus.
Order Dismissing Petition and Writ of Habeas Corpus.
Filed in the U.S. District Court Western Dist. of Washington, Northern Division Oct 16 1914 Frank L. Crosby, Clerk. By EML Deputy.
